# Accepted, documented risk - NOT a blanket suppression.
#
# Every CVE below is in usr/local/bin/subfinder's embedded Go dependencies
# (golang.org/x/crypto and the Go stdlib the v2.14.0 release binary was
# built against), not in this project's own code or its Python
# dependencies. subfinder is invoked as a subprocess for passive OSINT
# lookups only (see app/services/subdomain_scan.py) - it never accepts
# inbound connections, and the container it runs in has no capabilities
# beyond what platform/k8s/network-policy.yaml explicitly allows (see
# platform/README.md "Container image scan results" for the full
# rationale). The mechanical fix is bumping the Dockerfile's
# SUBFINDER_VERSION build arg once upstream publishes a release built
# against a patched Go toolchain - this file should be regenerated (not
# just re-approved) at that point by re-running:
#   trivy image --severity CRITICAL,HIGH --ignore-unfixed <image>
# and diffing against this list, since a NEW CVE not already listed here
# will still correctly fail the build.

